./.title: Introduction
./.body:
Trantrace
Trantrace is an open-source web-based application, which offers a simple and robust solution for large-scale continuous collaborative database translation.
     
       
     
Features

Enable every user to build own translation project with different permissions

Version control for your translation

Real-time task management

install-trantrace/requirements.html.title: Requirement
install-trantrace/requirements.html.body:
Requirement
Hardware
Necessary hardware largely depends on the size of translation databases and users online at the same time. Following is the minimal requirement:

CPU: Intel Core or Xeon 3GHz (or Dual Core 2GHz) or equal AMD CPU

cores: Single (Dual/Quad Core is recommended)

RAM: 4 GB (6 GB recommended)


Operating System

[info] We highly recommend to install Trantrace with docker-compose.


install with docker-compose: Even though lots of operating systems are supported by docker-compose and docker, Linux or Mac is recommended.

install from source: Ubuntu 16.04 is recommended.


Browser
We have only tested Trantrace on four browsers with the latest stable version, so others may have incompatibility issues.
Supported browser:

Google Chrome (>=70)
Firefox (>=67)
Edge (>=44)
IE11.

install-trantrace/install-with-docker-co.title: Install with Docker-compose
install-trantrace/install-with-docker-co.body:
Install Trantrace with Docker-compose
It is recommended to install Trantrace with docker-compose, which is isolated from dependency problems and easy to deploy.
Prerequisites
Docker is required for docker-compose, please make sure both are installed.

docker: Official Guide

docker-compose: Official Guide  


Configure

[warning] Please change the default MySQL root password in ".env" file for security.

Install
**[terminal]
# Build Trantrace
**[prompt sgidrylab@ubuntu]**[path ~]**[delimiter  $ ]**[command docker-compose build]
# Start Trantrace
**[prompt sgidrylab@ubuntu]**[path ~]**[delimiter  $ ]**[command docker-compose up -d]
For more operations, please see docker-compose official guide.
Setup
Login Trantrace as root with initial password 123456, and change password in GUI.

install-trantrace/install-from-source.ht.title: Install from Source
install-trantrace/install-from-source.ht.body:
Install from Source

Ubuntu 16.04 is recommended and the installation of dependencies and Trantrace is integrated. However, we still provide recommend procedures for users with other Linux distributions and Mac.
Ubuntu 16.04
**[terminal]
**[prompt sgidrylab@ubuntu]**[path ~]**[delimiter  $ ]**[command make install \
  MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=your_mysql_root_password \
  MYSQL_HOST=your_mysql_host \
  MYSQL_PORT=your_mysql_port]
If the default port (90) for Trantrace is occupied, please change 90 to other available port in conf/trantrace.apache.conf.
Other Linux distributions and Mac

Install mysql-server (>=5.7), and grant root (MySQL administrator) all privileges with root password. Then restart MySQL.
**[terminal]
**[prompt sgidrylab@centos]**[path ~]**[delimiter  $ ]**[command mysql -u root -p  ]
Enter password:
Welcome to the MySQL monitor.  Commands end with ; or \g.
Your MySQL connection id is 84975
Copyright (c) 2000, 2019, Oracle and/or its affiliates. All rights reserved.

**[prompt mysql>]**[command grant all PRIVILEGES on *.* to root@'%' identified by 'your_mysql_root_password' with grant option;]
Query OK, 0 rows affected, 1 warning (0.00 sec)

**[prompt mysql>]**[command flush privileges;]
Query OK, 0 row affected (0.00 sec)

**[prompt mysql>]**[command quit]
Bye
**[prompt sgidrylab@centos]**[path ~]**[delimiter  $ ]**[command sudo service mysql restart]

Install apache2.

Install PHP (>=7.1.3) and related PHP modules (bcmath, curl, igbinary, imap, ldap, mbstring, memcached, msgpack, mysql, xml, xmlrpc, zip).

If you want to change Trantrace port (default: 90), edit it in conf/trantrace.apache.conf.

Copy source code (src/) and configuration file (conf/trantrace.apache.conf) to corresponding folder.

Activate the website and restart apache2.


Setup
Login Trantrace as root with initial password 123456, and change password in GUI.

getting-started/roles.html.body:
Role
User role

There are two roles in Trantrace: administrator and general user.

  
    Role
    Permission
    Workspace
  
  
    administrator
    
      Add new user without registration.
      Activate or deactivate user account.
      Reset user password to 123456.
    
    Administration Interface
  
  
    general user
    
      Creat Own projects.
      Others depending on the role in project.
    
    User Interface
  


Project role
General users all share the same interface but have different workspace depending on the project role. There are four roles in one project: owner, translator, reviewer and guest (optional).
Once the project visibility is set to public, every logged in user is the project guest and they all can search released translation and open issues.

  
    Role
    Permission
    Workspace
  
  
    owner
    
      Specify setting, including deadline, priority, source and target language, visibility and members. 
      Upload the database files to be translated and large file should be splited to multiple small files.
      Assign entries to translator.
      Release version for qualified translation.
    
    Project Management
  
  
    
      Search released translations from joined project.
      Resolve issues.
    
    Released Projects
  
  
    translator
    
      Translate assigned entries from owner.
      Retranslate failed entries from reviewer.
    
    Translation Management
  
  
    
      Search released translations from joined project.

    Released Projects
  
  
    reviewer
    Review translation to decide whether to let it pass or not.

getting-started/workflow.html.title: Workflow
getting-started/workflow.html.body:
Workflow
     
       
     
Step 1. creation: user (owner) creates a project, uploads file and assigns entries' translation to translator.
Step 2. translation: translator continuously translates until approved by reviewer.
Step 3. review: reviewer reviews translation.
Step 4. release: all members cooperate to optimize translations until all are in good quality.
Step 1. Creation: user (owner) creates project, uploads file and assigns entries' translation to translator

Owner initiates the project:

Create a project: specify a source and target languages, deadline, priority, visibility and description, and designate project members (translator, reviewer, and guest).

Upload database files: only support comma-delimited (.csv) or tab-delimited (.tsv) text file and single-page spreadsheet (.xls or .xlsx) from Microsoft Excel.

Assign entries to translator.


     
       
     
Step 2. Translation: translator continuously translates until approved by reviewer

Translator needs continuous translation until approved by reviewer:

Translate assigned entries from owner.

     
       
     

Retranslate failed entries from reviewer.

     
       
     
Step 3. Review: reviewer reviews translation

Reviewer checks translation one by one and decides whether to let it pass or fail.
     
       
     
Step 4. Release: all members cooperate to optimize translations until all are in good quality.

Release version
Owner releases version according to progress.
     
       
     
Version iteration

Scenarios

Wrong translation: one project member opens an issue to point out the error of released translations.
     
       
     

More entries: owner uploads a new file to the project.
     
       
     



Procedures

Owner assigns entries to translator. 
Wrong translation: owner agrees on the issue and reassigns entry's translation to translator;
     
       
     
More entries: owner assigns the translation of new entries to translator (repeat step1).
     
       
     


Translator continuously translates until approved by reviewer (repeat step2)
Review reviews translation (repeat step3).
Owner releases version.

interface/root.html.title: Administration Interface
interface/root.html.body:
Administration Interface
The administrator account does not need to be registered. Just log in with the initial email (root) and password (123456). 

[warning] Please change the password immediately after log in.


How to change administrator password:


Click "Profile" in the upper right corner of the interface.
Click "Change Password".
Fill in the form.

     
       
     
User Management
Administrator can do nothing but manage users. If you want translation-related operations, please register a general user. 
     
       
     
Operations:

Add New User without Registration: click "New User".

Activate/Deactivate User: User can log in with this button on. Otherwise the user can not log in, but their records and operations are still reserved.

Reset Password: this button will reset the user password to "123456".

Search Existed User by Email and User Name.

interface/user.html.title: User Interface
interface/user.html.body:
User Interface
All users except administrator share the same interface but have different permissions on different panels according to project roles. 

Summary of unfinished tasks for every user
Dashboard
My Task   


Workspace for different project roles
Owner: Project Management
Translator: Translation Management
Reviewer: Review Management
All Members: Released Projects



Though all project members can search released translation and open issues in "Released Projects", only the owner has the right to resolve issues. 
     
       
                  
Summary of unfinished tasks
Dashboard

Dashboard counts the user's workload, complete percentage and unfinished numbers according to task categories (Assignment, Translation, Review and Issues) and project name. 
Click on the blue text in the last column and it will jump to unfinished tasks.
     
       
     
My Task

My task summaries unfinished tasks and updates every minute. 
These unfinished tasks are divided into five categories no matter which project is: 

'Unassigned' and 'Unresolved' for owner
'Untranslated' and 'Unretranslated' for translator
'Unreviewed' for reviewer. 

Click and it will jump to these unfinished tasks. For more detail, see entry status and issue status.
     
       
     
Workspace for different project roles
Owner: Project Management
Translator: Translation Management
Reviewer: Review Management
All Members: Released Projects

interface/owner-project-management.html.title: Owner: project management
interface/owner-project-management.html.body:
Owner: Project Management


Overview
Setting
Schedule
Upload
Release


Assignment


Overview

The projects created by you are listed here. "Total" is the total counts of project entries, and "Completed" is the percentage of entries with qualified translation. 

If you want to know more information about one project, Double click the row or click "Detail".

If you want to add a new project, click "New Project".

If the project is highlighted in pink, it means the project has not finished before the deadline.


     
       
     
Users can easily manage a project from four aspects: "Setting", "Schedule", "Upload" and "Release".
Setting

Setting shows the configuration when you created the project.

All settings are editable except the owner and creation date. Furthermore, the visibility level is only allowed to change from private to public. 

Delete the project is only allowed when nothing has been uploaded.

If more people want to join in, click Add Member > Edit. It is forbidden to delete members for record traceability now.


     
       
     
Schedule

Schedule is divided into two categories: project schedule and member schedule.

Project schedule summaries the progress of project stages (assignment, translation and review).

Member schedule calculates the complete percentage of each project member. 


     
       
     

Only owner is in charge of assignment, so the owner's task equals total counts of project entries (10).
Since translation review is not assigned, so the total reviewers' task equals to total counts of translated entries (5*80% + 2*100% = 6).

Furthermore, there is a shortcut for the owner's task: translation assignment ("Assignment") and issue resolvent ("Issues").
Upload

"Upload File" is the only way to add or append database entries in Trantrace. It has a specific requirement for the file.

Support file types:
comma-delimited (.csv) or tab-delimited (.tsv) text file.
Single-page spreadsheet (.xls or .xlsx) from Microsoft Excel.


File name:
Only support  letters (A-Za-z), numbers (0-9), dot (.), hypen (-), and underscore (_).
Make sure the extension is correct.


File size:
10MB or less.


Content:
The first row must be the header.
The first column must be unique.



     
       
     
Release

A new version is published with version id by clicking "New Version". Moreover, all historical versions are listed below.
     
       
     
Assignment

Assignment is the first step of task-based translation cooperation. Owner should assign entries to translator once the database file was uploaded.

Please see entry status for description of status.

     
       
     
Operations:

Assign one entry to one translator: fill in translator and click "Assign".

Assign multiple entries to one translator: select entries in the current page or "Search" results, then click "Batch Allocation".

Search entries by project name, keyword and status

interface/guest-released-projects.html.title: All: released projects
interface/guest-released-projects.html.body:
All Members: Released Projects


Overview
Issues


Overview
Released translations in which project you joined are displayed here. 
Operations:

Search released project by project name

List project versions: click "View" in "Versions" column

View entry's translation: click "Entries" to detail, then click "View" to see entry's translation.

Open an issue if found error: click "Open Issue", and the issue is only available for the latest version.


     
       
     
Issues
Issues of joined projects are listed here. Only owner has the right to resolve these issues.

Please see issue status for description of status.

     
       
     
Operations:

Search by project, keyword, and status

Resolve the issue: owner click "View" of unresolved issues, and click "Agree" to revive entry's translation or "Ignore" to close the issue if you thought the translation was good enough.

glossary.html.title: Glossary
glossary.html.body:
Glossary


Visibility level
Entry status
Issue status
Translation status


Visibility level



Level
Description




private
This project is only visible for project members (owner, translator, reviewer, and guest).


public
This project is visible for any logged-in user.



Entry status

An entry has five states: unassigned, untranslated, unretranslated, unreviewed and qualified.
Therefore, the sum of entry counts with five status equals to total counts of project entries.
Total= Total = Total=
∑unassigned+∑untranslated+∑unretranslated+∑unreviewed+∑qualified \sum unassigned + \sum untranslated + \sum unretranslated + \sum unreviewed + \sum qualified ∑unassigned+∑untranslated+∑unretranslated+∑unreviewed+∑qualified
     
       
     

  
    Entry Status
    Dashboard
    Workspace
    Worker
    Description
  
  
    unassigned
    Assignment
    Project Management > Assignment
    Owner
    Entry has not been assigned to translator.
  
  
    untranslated
    Translation
    Translation Management > Translation
    Translator
    Entry is assigned to you and has not been translated.
  
  
    unretranslated
    Translation Management > Retranslation
    Entry's latest translation is rejected by reviewer and has not been retranslated.
  
  
    unreviewed
    Review
    Review Management > Review 
    Reviewer
    Entry is translated and has not been reviewed. 
  
  
    qualified
    -
    -
    -
    Entry has been well translated and the translation can't be modified before version release.
  


Issue status

If one project member opened an issue about entry's wrong translation, the owner need to recheck the translation and reply it as soon as possible.
     
       
     
Once the issue was agreed, the translation status changed to "Error".

  
    Issue Status
    Dashboard
    Workspace
    Worker
    Description
  
  
    unresolved
    Issues
    Released Projects > Issues 
    Owner
    Owner has not replied to the issue yet.
  
  
    agreed
    -
    Owner agreed with the issue and revived the translation.
  
  
    ignored
    Owner disagreed with the issue and ignored it.
  


Translation status

     
       
     



Status
Description




Unreviewed
This translation has not been reviewed.


Passed
This translation passed the review.


Failed
This translation did not pass the review.


Error
This translation was released in a version, but someone thought it was wrong and the owner agreed.

**[terminal]
**[prompt sgidrylab@ubuntu]**[path ~]**[delimiter  $ ]**[command docker-compose build]
Building web
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "site-packages/docker/utils/build.py", line 96, in create_archive
**[error PermissionError: [Errno 13] Permission denied: 'trantrace/data/ca-key.pem']

**[error OSError: Can not read file in context: trantrace/data/ca-key.pem]
[3037] Failed to execute script docker-compose
Cause:

There is a data folder under the command execution directory, and you don't have permission to read it.
The data folder was automatically generated when you had started this service.

Solution:

If you want to keep previous records, skip this step and run "docker-compose up -d".
Delete the data folder, and rerun it.
